{
  "texts": [
    "Playing a card carries a risk because the team loses completely if three incorrect cards are played.",
    "Further, an incorrectly played card gets sent to the discard pile.",
    "Each number of a particular color only has so many copies, so if, for example, the last copy of a green 3 is lost, then the team loses out on not only playing the green 3 but also the green 4 and 5.",
    "This is the risk of playing or discarding.",
    "With these risks, and since reveal tokens are scarce, players ideally try to make assumptions about implicit information that a reveal may offer, and, ideally, the team converges to particular conventions."
  ]
}